## Commit & Pull Request Guidelines

- Commit subjects use conventional-commit-ish prefixes: `feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:`, `docs:`, `refactor:`.
- Subject line ≤ 72 chars. Body wraps at ~80 cols.
- One logical change per commit. If you can split it, split it.

## Security & Configuration Tips

- Never commit secrets. Use `.env.local` (gitignored) and document required env vars in a `.env.example`.
- Verify the `.gitignore` excludes `.claude/*` (except `settings.json`), `.gemini/`, and `.agents/`. The `cc-templates` `gitignore-additions.txt` covers this.
